result.execSummary:
The defendant Dennis M Tadeyeske was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Forgery-Uttering, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.38(2).
  • Theft-Business Setting >$10,000, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(b).
  • Identity Theft - Obtain Money or Credit, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.203(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Dennis M Tadeyeske in court with attorney Clarice Rosa Perkins.  Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.      The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

The sentence is to begin forthwith and the Defendant was taken into custody.
Count #1

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

5 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 0 days)
  -  2 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling. 
*No contact with:  Stamptech or the owners of the company.
*DNA sample to be provided.
*DNA surcharge is waived.
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*No presence on any premises whose primary business is serving or selling alcohol (i.e bars, taverns, or liquor stores).
*Mental Heath evaluation and an evaluation for any gambling addiction and treatment deemed appropriate. 
*Cognitive Intervention Program.
*Defendant may not obtain an employment position of fiduciary responsiblity for any business.
*Any other employment dealing with money must be approved with agent.

RESTITUTION:  $115,000.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - restitution to be paid before costs or fines); 
                            $105,000 paid to Stamptech
                            $10,000 paid Partners Mutual Insurance

COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);


Defendant is not eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);
